A Moyale Raha bus headed to Nairobi from Mandera has been attacked by suspected Al Shabaab gunmen in Mandera North. At least three passengers have been killed in the incident that occured at Sarman area in Mandera County on Wednesday. The management of Moyale Raha bus company said the vehicle left Mandera town in the morning only to be sprayed with bullets while on its way to Nairobi. "We are told the gunmen shot at the tyres but the driver sped off only to get into more gunfire ahead, " said a source at bus office. Mandera County Commissioner Onesmus Kathya has confirmed the incident but said his office is yet to get the details. "Something has happened but I am waiting finer details", said Kyatha. More follows..  